item.description:
In this project we tackle a classic binary-classification problem. Our ultimate goal is to build and train machine-learning models to detect fraudulent credit card transaction.
Credit card fraud is a form of identity fraud/theft. It happens when unauthorized transaction is made using a credit card without explicit permission from the card holder. There are various ways card fraud can be conducted&hellip;
 Fraudster can get discarded receipts or credit card statements that include your account number, and use that information to rack up fraudulent charges.
